{"title":"Sage Optimator Ti Hardtail gets Rowdier; Plus New Paint, Bar & Stem","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2024-sage-optimator-and-titanium-cockpit-components/","date":1714067137000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-1-1536x1047.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1047\" alt=\"2024 sage optimator titanium hardtail mountain bike\" /></p>\n<p>Sage Titanium Cycles is constantly tweaking their designs to keep them on trend and compatible with the latest components. The most recent update is for the Optimator, their titanium hardtail XC mountain bike. Geometry and frame details have been updated for modern trails and riding styles, with more travel and T-Type compatibility.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-2-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"2024 sage titanium optimator hardtail xc mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-2-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-2-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-2-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-2-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-2.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Up front, fork travel grows from 100mm to 120mm, and the head angle is relaxed to 67.5º.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-3-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details on the 2024 sage titanium optimator hardtail xc mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-3-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-3-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-3-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-3-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-3.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-10.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"570\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-10-1536x570.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details on the 2024 sage titanium optimator hardtail xc mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-10-1536x570.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-10-297x110.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-10-120x45.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-10-768x285.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-10-2048x760.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The dropouts and chainstay yoke are now 3D-printed, like many of their other models, and get the Owl logo embossed on the backside. A singlespeed version is also available with standard sliding dropouts (not 3D-printed).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1011\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-6-1536x1011.jpg\" alt=\"closeup details on the 2024 sage titanium optimator hardtail xc mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-6-1536x1011.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-6-297x196.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-6-120x79.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-6-768x506.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-optimator-titanium-hardtail-2024-update-6.jpg 2025w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These parts open up tire clearance to 29×2.4″. The rear brake hose now runs internally for a cleaner look, but sticks with a traditional port on the front of the frame rather than running through the headset. You can opt for full external routing, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Overall, the geometry is still racy, just updated to work with the longer travel fork. It’s 1x specific and clears up to a 36-tooth chainring, and there are two bottle cage bosses. Frames from $6,000.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Sage Titanium Riser Bar &amp; Stem</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-1-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"sage titanium riser handlebar for mountain bikes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-1-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-1-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-1.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Coming soon, this titanium handlebar comes in two versions – a 710mm wide flat bar with 7º backsweep and no rise, and a 800mm wide riser with 25mm rise and 13º backsweep. The latter weighs 349g with a Cerakote finish, which is probably only adding a few grams.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-2-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"color options for sage titanium riser handlebar for mountain bikes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-2-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-2-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-2-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-2-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-2.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like their frames, it can be had Raw or Cerakoted in your choice of solid colors (or otherwise customized to match a bike for an upcharge)…or just go for a stealth look. MSRP will range from $300 from $400, depending on rise and finish.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-3-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"sage bicycle stem\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-3-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-3-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-3-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-3-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-3.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>They’re also working on their own titanium stem for stealth cockpit setups, designed specifically for the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/chris-king-aeroset-1-2-integrated-internal-routing-headsets/\">Chris King Aeroset headsets</a>. It comes in at 175g for a 100mm length, and will be available in 80-120mm lengths with a -6º rise. It’s for drop bar bikes, not MTBs.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-4-1536x1152.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-4-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-4-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-4-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-4-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-titanium-stem-and-handlebars-4.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Spacers will use interlocking designs that let you remove them without undoing any brake hoses or cables, and may or may not be notched like the ones on the right to help them stack together perfectly…depends on the headset they’ll go with, they’ll likely have options for brands other than Chris King.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>New Standard Paint</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-standard-paint-cerakote-option-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-standard-paint-cerakote-option-2-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"sage titanium bikes standard paint option lets you choose any three colors in a preset pattern\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-standard-paint-cerakote-option-2-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-standard-paint-cerakote-option-2-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-standard-paint-cerakote-option-2-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-standard-paint-cerakote-option-2-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/sage-standard-paint-cerakote-option-2.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Technically, it’s Cerakote, not paint, but the new “standard paint” option lets you choose three colors to use in this pattern. Pick the top, middle, and bottom, and they’ll match the logo colors to the top color for a cohesive look. This option has a lower $1,200 upcharge (versus ~$2,000 and up for full custom), but still lets you choose the colors you want.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://sagetitanium.com\" target=\"_blank\">SageTitanium.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2024-sage-optimator-and-titanium-cockpit-components/\">Sage Optimator Ti Hardtail gets Rowdier; Plus New Paint, Bar &amp; Stem</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"674a93415756af313c1feb8c5781a717989e1d53ffad8e41388b397b3b0885ad","category":"Cycling"}